any_element.text: Tests for XSD 1.1 wildcard extensions

A number of tests, both valid and invalid, demonstrating use of the new
                XSD 1.1 features for wildcards, for example the notNamespace and notQName attributes.

Element Wildcard union with notQName="##defined"

Tests the spec note:
                Note: When one of the wildcards has defined in {disallowed names} and the other does not, 
                then defined is not included in the union. This may allow QNames that are not allowed by 
                either wildcard. This is to ensure that all unions are expressible. If defined is intended 
                to be included, then it is necessary to have it in both wildcards.
